  "prompt": "Do employees at Integrated Device have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "I don't have real-time data on work-life balance for employees at Integrated Device Technology (IDT). However, work-life balance can vary widely across different companies, departments, and positions. Factors that typically influence work-life balance include company culture, the type of work, management practices, workload, and personal circumstances.\n\nTo understand the specific work-life balance at IDT, you may want to consider:\n\n1. **Employee Reviews:** Websites like Glassdoor, Indeed, or LinkedIn often have employee reviews that discuss work-life balance.\n2. **Company Policies:** Look into IDT's official policies on flexible working hours, remote work options, and paid time off.\n3. **Job Role:** Certain positions, especially in tech, can have more demanding hours. This might be more prominent in roles such as senior management or project-based roles.\n4. **Department Differences:** Research if there are known differences between departments like engineering, sales, HR, etc. Some departments might have more intensive workloads than others.\n\nPlease keep in mind that individual experiences can vary greatly even within the same company, so it\u2019s important to gather as much information as possible from multiple sources.",
